title: New Kids in the Wild
subTitle: Cheetah cub Usana is born with the odds stacked against her, but she is lucky to have an amazing mother that will stop at nothing to keep her cubs safe.

title: New Kids in the Wild
subTitle: In Brazil's Serra da Capivara, a troop of capuchin monkeys welcome their latest member, baby Chico, who soon explores a forest full of excitement and danger whilst learning key skills that will allow him to survive and thrive.

title: New Kids in the Wild
subTitle: In India, Ravi the baby lion-tailed macaque faces life in a shrinking habitat and encroaching human world. Luckily, he has a caring mum, a protective dad, a playful sister, and numerous cousins, aunts and uncles who are watching over him.

title: River Monsters
subTitle: Hundreds died when the Sobral Santos sank on the Amazon, many of whom wer rumoured to have been eaten alive. Jeremy Wade retraces the doomed boat's last voyage to discover what was behind the event.

title: Extreme Africa
subTitle: The Southern Drylands is a journey into the most arid and extreme environments in the furthest reaches of southern Africa. Spectacular but treacherous places where almost no rain falls with incredibly resilient creatures.

title: Wild Africa: Rivers of Life
subTitle: On the Luangwa River, the law of the land is dictated by the ever-changing seasons and the constant cycle of life. In the wet season the Luangwa Valley is a green paradise, as the waters flow in abundance and lush green vegetation carpets the landscape. But in the dry season, when rains become but a distant memory, the greenery turns brown and the water levels drop by a foot per day.

title: Epic Animal Encounters
subTitle: In the Kruger National Park in South Africa, Dianne finds a boomslang and a chameleon in a duel on the tar road. Not a environment where they would encounter each other under any normal circumstances.

title: Jungle Planet
subTitle: Cameras capture the beauty, diversity and richness of the world's forests and jungles.

title: Deadliest South Africa
subTitle: Kurdt Greenwood's is on a quest is to seek out South Africa's 12 most deadly snakes and to educate and inspire people to see the value of these often misunderstood creatures.

title: Masai Mara: African Wildlife Stories
subTitle: The wildlife of the Maasai Mara reveals the raw beauty and realities of one of the most untamed lands, highlighting the daily struggle for survival and the balance between predator and prey.

subTitle: The surprising ways animals have adapted to ensure they make it to old age.

subTitle: The forests of California, notable for their size and diversity. Redwood trees thrive over the mountains while wildlife including black bears and squirrels fluorishes.

title: Battle of the Alphas
subTitle: Wildebeest battle for herd hierarchy, floppy fish fight it out on land and locusts give up their vegetarian ways in a frenzy of cannibalism. It all happens on the wild and wide-open landscape of South Africa.

title: Battle of the Alphas
subTitle: The latitudes south of the Sahara offer vastly different battlegrounds for a wide range of warriors. Male giraffes swing their heads like wrecking balls, zebras boast the most powerful kick in the animal kingdom, and chimpanzee warfare is eerily familiar.

title: Africa's Hunters
subTitle: Kamuti is a wise old leopard who has reigned over two square miles of prime territory in the Luangwa Valley for ten years, but now she is in trouble. At 13-years-old, Kamuti is one of the oldest leopards in the African bush, and she is not as effective a hunter as she used to be. Kamuti's problems are compounded by her neighbours, the Nsefu pride of lions, who steal her kills and attack her on sight.

title: Hot Life Africa
subTitle: Lion prey tends to feed when hunters are resting, which means when the sun is at its highest. A rise in temperature affects the behaviour of the animals living in these hot areas.
